olive oil
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet filo pastry
1 tbs milk
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet diced bacon
1 cucumber
1 onion
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons. Cut onion into wedges.

• Place onion and peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven tray, then sprinkle with Aussie spice blend.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast until tender, 18-20 minutes.
• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• When the veggies are done, remove from oven and transfer to a plate.
• Place filo pastry flat on the lined oven tray. Place roasted veggies in centre of the pastry, leaving a 4cm boarder around the edge. Sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese and cooked bacon.
• Carefully fold pastry edges over pumpkin, leaving the centre exposed. Brush edges of pastry with milk.
• Bake in the oven until golden, 15-20 minutes.

TIP: Use the same lined oven tray from the veggies to cook your pastry for extra flavour!

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, cucumber and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Slice pumpkin, bacon and Cheddar galette and divide between plates. Dollop chargrilled capsicum relish over galette.
• Serve with cucumber salad. Enjoy!